\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Overview views available after loading a VeloxChem HDF5 dataset in VIAMD. Top: the Summary window reports calculation metadata, geometry information, and interactive tables linked to the molecular view. Bottom left: the SCF and optimization panel exposes convergence histories for electronic and structural relaxation. Bottom right: the Critical Points panel summarizes density-topology analysis derived from the reconstructed electron density, including graph settings, counts by critical-point type, and an interactive table of extracted points.\relax }}{6}{figure.caption.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:summary}{{2}{6}{Overview views available after loading a VeloxChem HDF5 dataset in VIAMD. Top: the Summary window reports calculation metadata, geometry information, and interactive tables linked to the molecular view. Bottom left: the SCF and optimization panel exposes convergence histories for electronic and structural relaxation. Bottom right: the Critical Points panel summarizes density-topology analysis derived from the reconstructed electron density, including graph settings, counts by critical-point type, and an interactive table of extracted points.\relax }{figure.caption.4}{}}
