\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Representative electronic-structure visualizations in VIAMD. Top left: the default HOMO molecular-orbital representation generated upon loading a VeloxChem file. Top right: a green total-electron-density isosurface. Bottom left: an electron-density representation tinted by RESP charges. Bottom right: an alpha--beta density difference for an unrestricted calculation. Together, these examples show that the representation system can combine orbitals, densities, charge-derived coloring, and spin-density differences within the same interactive view.\relax }}{9}{figure.caption.6}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:electronic-landscape}{{3}{9}{Representative electronic-structure visualizations in VIAMD. Top left: the default HOMO molecular-orbital representation generated upon loading a VeloxChem file. Top right: a green total-electron-density isosurface. Bottom left: an electron-density representation tinted by RESP charges. Bottom right: an alpha--beta density difference for an unrestricted calculation. Together, these examples show that the representation system can combine orbitals, densities, charge-derived coloring, and spin-density differences within the same interactive view.\relax }{figure.caption.6}{}}
